    "default_locale": "en-US",
    "description": {
        "en-US": "Normally, when doing a standard CTRL-K search, aka a \"faceted\" search, the results default to sort by \"relevance\". I almost always change that to \"date\", but that choice is not remembered, and there is no way to change the default. This extension makes the change.\n\nThis does not apply to CTRL-SHIFT-F search, which already defaults to order by date.\n\nIf the latest version hasn't yet appeared here, you can always download it at <a href=\"http://lacinato.com/cm/software/extensions/srsbdnr\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://lacinato.com/cm/software/extensions/srsbdnr</a>"
    },
